ted financial and operating data of SpaceX has been prepared to reflect the retrospective combination of the companies for all periods presented."\n*   It further clarifies that the "consolidated financial statements have been prepared to reflect the retrospective combination of the net assets of the entities at their historical carrying amounts for all periods presented."\n*   The notes confirm this constitutes a **"change in reporting entity."**\n\n### **4. Specific Details on the Combination Mechanics**\n*   **Merger Timeline:**\n    *   X Holdings was acquired by xAI effective **March 28, 2025** ("X Merger").\n    *   X.AI Holdings Corp. (xAI) was acquired by SpaceX effective **February 2, 2026** ("xAI Merger").\n*   **Exchange Ratios (Applied Retroactively):**\n    *   **X Merger:** Each share of X Common Stock was converted to 2.776 shares of xAI Common Stock.\n    *   **xAI Merger:** Each share of xAI Common Stock was converted to 0.1433 shares of SpaceX Common Stock (on a pre-split basis).\n*   **Retroactive Share Presentation:** As a result of these mergers, historical share counts for X, X.AI Corp., and xAI Common Stock are presented in the financial statements as if they had been converted into SpaceX Common Stock at the applicable exchange rates for all periods presented.\n*   **Exception - Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock:** xAI\'s Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was legally outstanding as a separate class in all historical periods prior to the merger. Therefore, it is **not** recast on an as-converted basis. Its conversion into SpaceX Common Stock is recognized only in the period the exchange actually occurred (Q1 2026).\n\n### **Summary Statement from the Prospectus:**\n> "The consolidated financial statements of SpaceX have been retrospectively recast for all periods presented to include (i) the historical results of X.AI Holdings Corp... and X Holdings Corp.... because these transactions were between entities under common control, and (ii) a five-for-one stock split... This presentation constitutes a change in reporting entity."\n\n**Sources:**\nAll information is derived from the sections labeled **[SECTION: PREAMBLE]** and **[SECTION: PREAMBLE]** within the provided document chunks.',
